parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel becomes firm or difficult to turn
the vehicle loses power steering functionality
the steering wheel seizes or locks up
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
and the instrument panel lights flicker.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduction or disablement of steering assist can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering assist reduced or disabled warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel becomes firm or difficult to turn
the vehicle loses power steering functionality
the steering wheel seizes or locks up
and the instrument panel lights flicker.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ESC warning light is illuminated
the vehicle loses traction and stability
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
and the instrument panel lights flicker.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become hard or spongy, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal is hard to press
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vacuum pump can cause the brake pedal to become hard or spongy, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal is hard to press
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vacuum pump makes a clicking sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the trailer brake system can cause the brake pedal to become hard or spongy, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The trailer brake system warning light illuminates
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal is hard to press
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes at low speeds can cause the vehicle to be unable to stop or slow down, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal is hard to press
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of issues, including loss of power, engine stalling, and failure of critical systems like steering and brakes, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Flickering or flashing dash lights
loss of power
engine stalling
failure of cruise control
media
and cabin functions
and sudden resistance in steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Trailer brake system issues can cause distractions, accidents, and loss of control while towing.
symptoms: Repeated warnings of "Service Trailer Brake System"
inability to silence the warning
and failure of the trailer brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear defroster and window issues can cause fires, shattered windows, and reduced visibility while driving.
symptoms: Smoke or fire from the rear defroster
shattered rear window
and static or sizzling sounds from the rear defroster.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition and starting issues can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Difficulty starting the vehicle
ignition lock cylinder failure
and failure to start the vehicle.
